# UI Elements Catalog

The authoritative UI inventory is [`docs/UI_ELEMENTS.md`](docs/UI_ELEMENTS.md). Every agent **must** use it when adding or changing user-facing behavior.

## Before UI work

1. Read `docs/UI_ELEMENTS.md` to learn existing elements, selectors, and patterns.
2. Reuse documented selectors and shared components (`.btn`, `.panel`, `item-hash`) — do not invent parallel hooks.
3. Cross-check [`INTERFACE_FEATURES.md`](docs/INTERFACE_FEATURES.md) for feature status; cross-check [`DESIGN_SYSTEM.md`](docs/DESIGN_SYSTEM.md) for visual tokens.

## After any UI change (required)

Update `docs/UI_ELEMENTS.md` in the **same task** when you:

- Add or remove a button, panel, field, modal, or dynamic template
- Change an element's `id`, class, selector, label, or wired behavior
- Add or rename an icon sprite symbol

Each new or changed row needs: **Name**, **Selector**, **Page**, **Purpose**, **Behavior**, **Source**.

If a feature adds backend-only code today but exposes UI later, add a placeholder row marked *(planned)* so the catalog stays complete.

## New element checklist

- [ ] Stable `id` or class documented in the catalog
- [ ] Entry added/updated in `docs/UI_ELEMENTS.md`
- [ ] `INTERFACE_FEATURES.md` updated if user-visible behavior changed
- [ ] Nielsen heuristics satisfied (`nielsen-heuristics.mdc`)

## Do not

- Ship new UI without a catalog entry
- Duplicate an existing element under a new name without documenting both
- Leave removed elements listed in the catalog
